 perpendicular polarization expected. If outflows are\ncollimated by the torus inner walls, they must not be optically thick (tau < 1)\nin order to preserve the polarization dichotomy. The wind's optical depth is\nfound not to play a critical role for the degree of polarization of type-2\nthermal AGNs but it has a significant impact on the type-1/type-2 polarization\ndichotomy when the optical depth exceeds tau = 0.3.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Sep 2012 14:50:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
{"id":"1209.2918","submitter":"R\\u{a}zvan Valentin Florian","authors":"C\\u{a}t\\u{a}lin V. Rusu, R\\u{a}zvan V. Florian","title":"A new class of metrics for spike trains","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Rusu, C. V., & Florian, R. V. (2014). A new class of metrics for\n  spike trains. Neural Computation, 26(2), 306-348","doi":"10.1162/NECO_a_00545","report-no":null,"categories":"cs.IT cs.NE math.IT q-bio.NC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The distance between a pair of spike trains, quantifying the differences\nbetween them, can be measured using various metrics. Here we introduce a new\nclass of spike train metrics, inspired by the Pompeiu-Hausdorff distance, and\ncompare them with existing metrics. Some of our new metrics (the modulus-metric\nand the max-metric) have characteristics that are qualitatively different than\nthose of classical metrics like the van Rossum distance or the Victor & Purpura\ndistance. The modulus-metric and the max-metric are particularly suitable for\nmeasuring distances between spike trains where information is encoded in\nbursts, but the number and the timing of spikes inside a burst does not carry\ninformation. The modulus-metric does not depend on any parameters and can be\ncomputed using a fast algorithm, in a time that depends linearly on the number\nof spikes in the two spike trains. We also introduce localized versions of the\nnew metrics, which could have the biologically-relevant interpretation of\nmeasuring the differences between spike trains as they are perceived at a\nparticular moment in time by a neuron receiving these spike trains.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Sep 2012 14:55:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Aug 2013 19:43:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 17 Jan 2014 12:46:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-20"}
